Photorealistic style: A dramatic still life composition on a dark wooden table featuring a pristine orange cut in half revealing its vibrant segments, placed next to a perfectly ripe yellow banana, both fruits illuminated by moody directional lighting casting long shadows. Behind them, slightly out of focus, sits an old-fashioned brass balance scale with its pans tilted unevenly. The scene has rich, saturated colors with a chiaroscuro effect reminiscent of Dutch Golden Age paintings, emphasizing the absurdity of comparing fundamentally different things. Droplets of citrus juice glisten on the table surface, and the atmosphere suggests a moment of contemplation about unfair comparisons.
